The paper deals with lower bounds for counting Hamiltonian cycles, which is a problem in graph theory and combinatorics. The techniques used involve matrix rank and pathwidth, which are concepts commonly studied in theoretical computer science. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.CC (Computational Complexity), cs.CG (Computational Geometry), cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics), and cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory).
